How to run the programs

Decoder (baseline):

1. Goto terminal and run the program
python decode > translations

2. To calculate the score, run:
python compute-model-score < translations

3. If the above statement gives an error (in some version of windows, it throws an error), then try
Get-Content translations | python compute-model-score

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Decoder with Reordering:

1. Goto terminal and run the program
python decoder_reorder > translations_reordered

2. To calculate the score, run:
python compute-model-score < translations_reordered

3. If the above statement gives an error (in some version of windows, it throws an error), then try
Get-Content translations_reordered | python compute-model-score

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Decoder with Vector Coverage

1. Goto terminal and run the program
python decode_cover > translations_decode_cover

2. To calculate the score, run:
python compute-model-score < translations_decode_cover

3. If the above statement gives an error (in some version of windows, it throws an error), then try
Get-Content translations_decode_cover | python compute-model-score

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Decode with Travelling Salesman Problem

1. Goto terminal and run the program
python decode_tsp > translations_tsp

2. To calculate the score, run:
python compute-model-score < translations_tsp

3. If the above statement gives an error (in some version of windows, it throws an error), then try
Get-Content translations_tsp | python compute-model-score
